02/05/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Panos Beglitis expressed satisfaction Thursday (1 May) with the fact that Turkey has completed the legislative process of ratifying the Ottawa Treaty banning anti-personnel mines. Greece and Turkey plan to jointly submit the documentation at the UN Secretariat in New York, as a symbolic gesture of their accession to the international treaty, according to Beglitis. (MPA - 01/05/03)
